Package: BoolNetPerturb
Title: Perturb Boolean Networks
Version: 0.2
Authors@R: c(person(
    "ME", "Martinez-Sanchez", email = "mariana.martinez@c3.unam.mx", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("JA", "Arias Del Angel", role = c("aut")) )
Description: The BoolNetPerturb package adds functions to BoolNet for
    perturbing Boolean Regulatory Networks. This functions can be used
    for the study of biological systems. This package is capable of
    labeling states, simulating multiple knock-outs and over-expressions,
    simulating fixed and transient perturbations in the states and
    trajectory of a network, and converting to a continuous ODE system.
Depends:
    R (>= 3.1.0),
    BoolNet (>= 2.1.1)
Suggests: testthat, deSolve
SystemRequirements: Perl (>=5)
License: MIT
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.1.0
VignetteBuilder: knitr
